title: Draft - Hyderabad Biriyani
description:
Hyderabadi Biryani is a world-famous dish that originated in the kitchens of the Nizams of Hyderabad.
It is a blend of Mughlai and Deccani culinary traditions, symbolizing royal heritage.
This biryani is traditionally made with basmati rice, marinated meat (often mutton or chicken), and aromatic spices.
It is cooked using the "dum" (slow steam) method to infuse rich flavors.
There are two main styles: Kacchi (raw marinated meat layered with rice) and Pakki (cooked meat and rice).
Hyderabadi Biryani is not just food—it's a cultural emblem of Hyderabad’s rich history and diversity.
